President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. Brian T. Baenig is nominated for Assistant Secretary for Congressional Relations at the Department of Agriculture. Meg Bartley is nominated for Judge at the United States Court of Appeals for Veterans Claims. Mary Beth Leonard is nominated for Ambassador to the Republic of Mali at the Department of State. Gloria Wilson Shelton is nominated for Judge at the United States Court of Appeals for Veterans Claims. Additionally, Christopher Che is appointed as a Member of the President's Council on Jobs and Competitiveness. Linda K. Kerber is appointed as a Member of the Permanent Committee for the Oliver Wendell Holmes Devise. Judge Trina Thompson is appointed as a Member of the Coordinating Council on Juvenile Justice and Delinquency Prevention.